Package: ferm-nftables
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${python3:Depends}, iptables, nftables
Conflicts: ferm
Replaces: ferm
Description: ferm syntax parser for iptables-nftables
 ferm is a Python implementation that parses firewall rules in ferm
 syntax and generates iptables-nftables commands. It provides the same
 configuration syntax as the original ferm tool but uses iptables-nftables
 (nftables backend) instead of iptables-legacy.
 .
 Features:
  - Parses ferm configuration files
  - Generates iptables-nftables commands
  - Supports most ferm syntax including tables, chains, targets,
    protocols, addresses, ports, and modules
  - Compatible with iptables-restore format
  - Includes systemd service
